</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h3 id="5.-Analysis-of-Poverty-&amp;-Starvation">5. Analysis of Poverty &amp; Starvation<a class="anchor-link" href="#5.-Analysis-of-Poverty-&amp;-Starvation">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>In this analysis we are now comparing the starvation and poverty variables, because we want to investigate the relationship between the two variables.</p>
<p>Variables used:</p>
<ol>
<li>Poverty</li>
<li>Starvation</li>
<li>Year</li>
</ol>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[11]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataSkipped</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">&quot;Year&quot;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">dataSkipped</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">&quot;Poverty Annual Change&quot;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">label</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;Poverty&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dataSkipped</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">&quot;Year&quot;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">dataSkipped</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">&quot;Hunger Annual Change&quot;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">label</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;Starvation&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<h4 id="Conclusion">Conclusion<a class="anchor-link" href="#Conclusion">&#182;</a></h4><p>Upon analysis of the data, we find that the trend mostly remains linear and starvation follows poverty as well, and thus also used the scatter plot to highlight the dependency of starvation on poverty with unemployment added as hue to emphasize upon the effect density.</p>
<ul>
<li>Less power to buy essentials, means more starvation periods in the country</li>
<li>Poverty is on the highest density when there is unemployment</li>
</ul>

</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h3 id="1.-Forecasting-Food-Prices-Using-Prophet">1. Forecasting Food Prices Using Prophet<a class="anchor-link" href="#1.-Forecasting-Food-Prices-Using-Prophet">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="i.-Forecasting-Wheat-Prices-In-Balochistan">i. Forecasting Wheat Prices In Balochistan<a class="anchor-link" href="#i.-Forecasting-Wheat-Prices-In-Balochistan">&#182;</a></h4>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Using prophet wanted to identify the trend of the ongoing prices of essential foods which are common to Pakistani's to predict how starvation is going to be affected till 2023. Specifically have chosen Balochistan province as a candidate for this prediction test.</p>
<p>Variables Used:</p>
<ol>
<li>Food Product</li>
<li>Province</li>
<li>Date</li>
<li>Price</li>
</ol>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[13]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">prophet</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">Prophet</span>
<span class="n">foodPrices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">r</span><span class="s1">&#39;./WFP Food Prices In Pakistan.csv&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">foodPrices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">foodPrices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="n">wheatBalochistan</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">foodPrices</span><span class="p">[(</span><span class="n">foodPrices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Product&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Wheat flour - Retail&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">&amp;</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">foodPrices</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Province&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Balochistan&#39;</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="n">wheatBalochistanPrices</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">wheatBalochistan</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;Date&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Price&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">wheatBalochistanPrices</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;ds&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">&#39;y&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">m</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Prophet</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">interval_width</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.95</span><span class="p">)</span> 
<span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wheatBalochistanPrices</span><span class="p">)</span> 
<span class="n">future</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">make_future_dataframe</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">periods</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1000</span><span class="p">)</span> 
<span class="n">forecast</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">future</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">forecast</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s1">&#39;ds&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;yhat&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;yhat_lower&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;yhat_upper&#39;</span><span class="p">]]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tail</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">confirmed_forecast_plot</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">m</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">forecast</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<h3 id="2.-Forecasting-Starvation-Using-Regressions">2. Forecasting Starvation Using Regressions<a class="anchor-link" href="#2.-Forecasting-Starvation-Using-Regressions">&#182;</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>To determine the relationship between starvation and the year</p>

</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="1.-Linear-Regression:">1. Linear Regression:<a class="anchor-link" href="#1.-Linear-Regression:">&#182;</a></h4><p>Linear regression uses the relationship between the data-points to draw a straight line through all them. This line can be used to predict future values.</p>
<p>Variables used:</p>
<ol>
<li>Starvation</li>
<li>Year</li>
</ol>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[14]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">scipy</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">stats</span>
<span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dataWhole</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Hunger Annual Change&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dataWhole</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Year&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">slope</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">intercept</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">p</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">std_err</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">stats</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linregress</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">predictFutureValue</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">):</span>
  <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">slope</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">intercept</span>

<span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">list</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">predictFutureValue</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;The r values is:&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">r</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

<h4 id="Conclusion:">Conclusion:<a class="anchor-link" href="#Conclusion:">&#182;</a></h4><ul>
<li>The r value ranges from -1 to 1, where 0 means no relationship, and 1 (and -1) means 100% related.</li>
<li>In linear regression terms the <strong><em>r</em></strong> is -0.03170809032360416 which indicates the data provided is not suitable</li>
</ul>
<p>Thus, we shift towards polynomial regression to predict better results.</p>
<p>Note: Any r value that resides around 0 indicates the dataset provided is not suitable for linear regression</p>

</div>

<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="2.-Polynomial-Regression:">2. Polynomial Regression:<a class="anchor-link" href="#2.-Polynomial-Regression:">&#182;</a></h4><p>Polynomial regression, like linear regression, uses the relationship between the variables x and y to find the best way to draw a line through the data points.</p>
<p>Used when a straight line through all data points condition doesn't meet.</p>

</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell   ">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In&nbsp;[16]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
     <div class="CodeMirror cm-s-jupyter">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">sklearn.metrics</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">r2_score</span>

<span class="c1"># Predict futre values using the model</span>
<span class="n">model</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">poly1d</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">polyfit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="n">line</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">linspace</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mf">0.4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">line</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">line</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;R-Squared Value: &quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">r2_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>

<h4 id="Conclusion:">Conclusion:<a class="anchor-link" href="#Conclusion:">&#182;</a></h4><p>R-Squared value is important to know how well the relationship between the values of the x- and y-axis is, if there are no relationship the polynomial regression can not be used to predict anything.</p>
<ul>
<li>The r-squared value ranges from 0 to 1, where 0 means no relationship, and 1 means 100% related.</li>
<li>Here we find R-Squared value to be 0.08830098332986092 which means a bad relationship</li>
</ul>
<p>Now moving on to multiple linear regression, so we can add multiple factors to make the results more accurate.</p>

<h4 id="3.-Multiple-Linear-Regression">3. Multiple Linear Regression<a class="anchor-link" href="#3.-Multiple-Linear-Regression">&#182;</a></h4><p>Multiple regression is like linear regression, but with more than one independent value, meaning that we try to predict a value based on two or more variables.</p>
<p>Variables Used:</p>
<ul>
<li>Inflation Annual Change</li>
<li>Economic Annual Change</li>
<li>Population Growth Rate Annually</li>
<li>Unemployment Annual Change</li>
<li>Poverty Annual Change</li>
<li>Hunger Annual Change</li>
</ul>

</div>

<span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dataWhole</span><span class="p">[[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Inflation Annual Change&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Economic Annual Change&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Population Growth Rate&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Poverty Annual Change&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">&#39;Unemployment Per Year&#39;</span><span class="p">]]</span>
<span class="n">y</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dataWhole</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">&#39;Hunger Annual Change&#39;</span><span class="p">]</span>
